#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/advanced-effect-event-deps.md
M|rules|title: Do Not Put Effect Events in Dependency Arrays
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids unnecessary effect re-runs and lint errors
M|rules|tags: advanced, hooks, useEffectEvent, dependencies, effects
M|rules|Effect Event functions do not have a stable identity. Their identity intentionally changes on every render. Do not include the function returned by `useEffectEvent` in a `useEffect` dependency array. 
M|rules|**Incorrect (Effect Event added as a dependency):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'react'
M|rules|function ChatRoom({ roomId, onConnected }: {
M|rules|roomId: string
M|rules|onConnected: () => void
M|rules|}) {
M|rules|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|rules|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|rules|connection.connect()
M|rules|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|rules|}, [roomId, handleConnected])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Including the Effect Event in dependencies makes the effect re-run every render and triggers the React Hooks lint rule.
M|rules|**Correct (depend on reactive values, not the Effect Event):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'react'
M|rules|function ChatRoom({ roomId, onConnected }: {
M|rules|roomId: string
M|rules|onConnected: () => void
M|rules|}) {
M|rules|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|rules|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|rules|connection.connect()
M|rules|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|rules|}, [roomId])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Reference: [React useEffectEvent: Effect Event in deps](https://react.dev/reference/react/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps)